<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Luckify Me — Quantitative Model Update 2026</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --black:      #0C0C0C;
    --orange:     #E07840;
    --orange-dim: #C4693A;
    --cream:      #F7F4EF;
    --warm-white: #FDFCFA;
    --gray-1:     #1C1C1C;
    --gray-2:     #3A3834;
    --gray-3:     #7A7670;
    --gray-4:     #B8B4AE;
    --gray-5:     #E2DED8;
    --green:      #2D6A4A;
    --gold:       #A07828;
  }

  html { background: var(--black); }

  body {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--warm-white);
    color: var(--gray-1);
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  /* ── TOP ACCENT ── */
  .top-bar {
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--orange);
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  header {
    padding: 52px 56px 44px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    align-items: end;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .brand-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--orange);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 38px;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--black);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--orange-dim);
  }

  .header-meta {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    margin-top: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .header-right {
    text-align: right;
  }

  .edition-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* ── STAT ROW ── */
  .stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }

  .stat {
    padding: 28px 28px 24px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    position: relative;
  }
  .stat:last-child { border-right: none; }

  .stat-num {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    color: var(--orange);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .stat-sub {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--gray-4);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* ── MAIN CONTENT ── */
  main {
    padding: 0 56px;
  }

  /* ── SECTION ── */
  .section {
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }
  .section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    height: 1px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--gray-5);
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--gray-2);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  p strong { color: var(--black); font-weight: 600; }

  /* ── CALLOUT ── */
  .callout {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--orange);
    background: #FEF6EF;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 18px 0;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .callout-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .callout p {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--gray-1);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* ── TWO COL ── */
  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  /* ── SIGNAL PILLS ── */
  .signals {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .signal-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 110px 120px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .signal-name {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--black);
  }

  .signal-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 5px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .badge-green  { background: #E8F5EE; color: var(--green); }
  .badge-red    { background: #FAECEC; color: #B22222; }
  .badge-gold   { background: #FBF4E4; color: var(--gold); }
  .badge-gray   { background: var(--gray-5); color: var(--gray-3); }
  .badge-orange { background: #FEF0E6; color: var(--orange-dim); }

  .signal-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── FLAGSHIP BOX ── */
  .flagship {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .flag-cell {
    padding: 24px 20px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .flag-cell.before { background: var(--cream); }
  .flag-cell.arrow  { background: var(--warm-white); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-left: 1px solid var(--gray-5); border-right: 1px solid var(--gray-5); }
  .flag-cell.after  { background: #FEF6EF; }

  .flag-tag {
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .flag-cell.before .flag-tag { color: var(--gray-3); }
  .flag-cell.after  .flag-tag { color: var(--orange); }

  .flag-num {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 44px;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .flag-cell.before .flag-num { color: var(--black); }
  .flag-cell.after  .flag-num { color: var(--orange); }

  .flag-sub {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
  }
  .flag-cell.after .flag-sub { color: #C4793A; }

  .arrow-icon {
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  /* ── MARKET TABLE ── */
  .market-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: 18px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .market-table th {
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }

  .market-table td {
    padding: 12px 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    vertical-align: top;
    color: var(--gray-2);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .market-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .market-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--cream); }

  .market-table td:first-child {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--black);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .status-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* ── ROADMAP ── */
  .roadmap {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .road-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 36px 1fr auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }
  .road-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .road-num {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    align-self: stretch;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: white;
    width: 36px;
  }
  .road-num.done   { background: var(--green); }
  .road-num.active { background: var(--orange); }
  .road-num.next   { background: var(--gold); }
  .road-num.future { background: var(--gray-4); }

  .road-content {
    padding: 13px 16px;
  }
  .road-title {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .road-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .road-status {
    padding: 0 16px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .road-status.done   { color: var(--green); }
  .road-status.active { color: var(--orange); }
  .road-status.next   { color: var(--gold); }
  .road-status.future { color: var(--gray-4); }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  footer {
    padding: 28px 56px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .footer-brand {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-4);
  }

  .footer-note {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--gray-4);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── PRINT / SHARE ── */
  @media print {
    body { max-width: 100%; }
    .top-bar { print-color-adjust: exact; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; }
    .stat-num, .flag-num { print-color-adjust: exact; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; }
  }

  /* ── MOBILE ── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    header {
      padding: 32px 24px 28px;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    h1 { font-size: 28px; }

    .header-right { text-align: left; }

    .stats {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
    .stat {
      padding: 20px 18px 16px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    }
    .stat:nth-child(2) { border-right: none; }
    .stat:nth-child(3) { border-bottom: none; }
    .stat:nth-child(4) { border-right: none; border-bottom: none; }
    .stat-num { font-size: 28px; }

    main { padding: 0 24px; }

    .section { padding: 28px 0; }

    h2 { font-size: 19px; }

    p { font-size: 13.5px; max-width: 100%; }

    .flagship {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: auto auto auto;
    }
    .flag-cell.arrow {
      border-left: none;
      border-right: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      padding: 10px;
    }
    .arrow-icon {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
      display: inline-block;
    }
    .flag-num { font-size: 36px; }

    .signal-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 6px;
      padding: 14px 14px;
    }
    .signal-name { font-size: 13px; }
    .signal-desc { font-size: 12px; }

    .market-table thead { display: none; }
    .market-table, .market-table tbody,
    .market-table tr, .market-table td { display: block; width: 100%; }
    .market-table tr {
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      border-radius: 4px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .market-table tr:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .market-table td {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      padding: 10px 14px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .market-table td:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .market-table td:first-child {
      background: var(--cream);
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .road-row { grid-template-columns: 36px 1fr; }
    .road-status { display: none; }
    .road-title { font-size: 13px; }
    .road-desc { font-size: 11.5px; }

    footer {
      padding: 24px 24px;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 6px;
    }
  }

  /* ── ANIMATIONS ── */
  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .stats, header, .section {
    animation: fadeUp 0.5s ease both;
  }
  header        { animation-delay: 0.05s; }
  .stats        { animation-delay: 0.15s; }
  .section:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
  .section:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.25s; }
  .section:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
  .section:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.35s; }
  .section:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="top-bar"></div>

<!-- HEADER -->
<header>
  <div>
    <div class="brand-label">Luckify Me</div>
    <h1>Quantitative Model<br><em>Update — 2026</em></h1>
    <div class="header-meta">March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; PGA Tour Golf &nbsp;·&nbsp; Findings & Strategy Summary</div>
  </div>
  <div class="header-right">
    <div class="edition-tag">Confidential &nbsp;·&nbsp; Q1 2026</div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- STATS -->
<div class="stats">
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Signal Accuracy</div>
    <div class="stat-num">64.9%</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">correct direction on unseen data</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Confidence Level</div>
    <div class="stat-num">99.7%</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">probability signals are not random</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Validated Signals</div>
    <div class="stat-num">254</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">high-confidence edges after correction</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Combinations Tested</div>
    <div class="stat-num">7,304</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">variable combinations rigorously tested</div>
  </div>
</div>

<main>

  <!-- 01 ORIGIN -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">01 &nbsp; Where We Started</div>
    <h2>An Honest Starting Point</h2>
    <p>When we began testing in golf, we broke even. That is worth saying plainly — and it is also the point. We were in the variable discovery phase: systematically isolating which factors produced statistically measurable effects before any capital was deployed at scale. Most operations skip this step. We did not.</p>
    <p>Breaking even during hypothesis testing is not a failure — it is what rigorous model development looks like. You do not scale until the variables are validated. <strong>That phase is now complete.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <!-- 02 VALIDATION -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">02 &nbsp; Validation Results</div>
    <h2>What the Data Confirmed</h2>
    <p>Every surviving signal was stress-tested against 2025–2026 data the model had never seen — a methodology known as out-of-sample validation, and the standard by which quantitative models are judged in academic research and professional finance. It is specifically designed to expose false positives and data artifacts that look real in training but collapse on new data.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">Key Finding</div>
      <p>64.9% of signals predicted the correct directional outcome on unseen data (vs. 50% expected by chance). A binomial probability test on this result yields <strong>p &lt; 0.003</strong> — well below the p &lt; 0.05 threshold used in peer-reviewed research to establish statistical significance. Put simply: there is a <strong>99.7% probability</strong> these edges are real. Additionally, all signals passed Benjamini-Hochberg correction — a method that specifically guards against false discoveries when testing large numbers of variables simultaneously.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flagship">
      <div class="flag-cell before">
        <div class="flag-tag">Training Data</div>
        <div class="flag-num">−2.06</div>
        <div class="flag-sub">strokes · adjusted effect size</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flag-cell arrow">
        <div class="arrow-icon">→</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flag-cell after">
        <div class="flag-tag">Out-of-Sample · 2025–26</div>
        <div class="flag-num">−2.94</div>
        <div class="flag-sub">signal strengthened on new data</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:13px;color:var(--gray-3);">Effect size retention of 72% out-of-sample. Industry benchmark for a robust signal is 30–40%. Signals that strengthen on new data — rather than decay — are rare and indicate a structural, not coincidental, relationship.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 03 SIGNALS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">03 &nbsp; Signal Structure</div>
    <h2>What the Model Identified</h2>
    <p>One proprietary variable category emerged as the dominant structural predictor across the dataset — statistically significant in 7 of the top 7 most consistent signal types identified. It is absent from every mainstream sports pricing model in existence, meaning it represents an unpriced factor: a measurable variable with demonstrable predictive power that the market has not yet discovered or incorporated.</p>
    <p>Within it, five distinct phases were identified and classified by their reproducibility and effect direction:</p>

    <div class="signals">
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Green Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-green">Consistent Positive</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Statistically significant positive effect across multiple rounds. adj. p ≈ 0.000 in peak combination. Sample size n=462 — large enough to rule out chance.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Amplifier Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-gold">Round-Dependent</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Largest effect sizes in dataset — both positive and negative. Direction is determined by round context. Statistically significant in both directions; must be used with round data.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Red Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-red">Reliable Negative</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Negative performance effect confirmed in 122 of 182 players (67%) in Round 2. Player-level consistency at this rate is statistically improbable by chance. Replicated out-of-sample.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Conditional Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-orange">Cycle-Dependent</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Effect direction determined by position within the broader cycle. Statistically significant in both halves with opposing signs. n=546 — one of the largest validated cells in the dataset.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Noise Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-gray">Removed</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Failed directional replication on out-of-sample data across 4 of 4 test signals. Removed from model. This is the process working as intended.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 04 MARKETS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">04 &nbsp; Market Strategy</div>
    <h2>Finding the Most Exploitable Markets</h2>
    <p>A validated signal is only valuable if it can be deployed in a market where the edge exceeds the friction of execution. Different betting formats have different levels of pricing efficiency — the degree to which the market has already incorporated available information. We are systematically measuring our edge-to-efficiency ratio across formats to identify where the model has the highest exploitable advantage.</p>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-bottom:18px;">
      <div class="callout-label">Why Group Size Matters</div>
      <p>Bookmakers price 2-ball markets with high precision — two players, one outcome, relatively simple math. As group size increases, the number of possible outcome combinations grows exponentially, and the book's pricing model degrades proportionally. This is the <strong>combinatorial complexity problem</strong>: the larger the group, the harder it is for the market to hold accurate prices across all outcomes simultaneously. Our model exploits exactly this degradation. Early data suggests 3-ball markets carry meaningfully larger edges than 2-ball for this reason — and 6-ball formats may represent the highest inefficiency tier of all. Testing is ongoing.</p>
    </div>

    <table class="market-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Market</th>
          <th>Pricing Efficiency</th>
          <th>Our Edge</th>
          <th>Status</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>2-Ball Matchups</td>
          <td>High — books price head-to-head with precision. Limited outcome combinations keep margins tight.</td>
          <td>Lower relative edge. Our variables are unpriced but the book's baseline accuracy compresses the return.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:#FEF0E6;color:#C4693A;">Active Testing</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>3-Ball Matchups</td>
          <td>Moderate — three-way pricing introduces combinatorial complexity the book cannot fully resolve.</td>
          <td>Higher edge than 2-ball. Early data shows meaningfully larger returns as book mispricing increases with group size.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:#FEF0E6;color:#C4693A;">Active Testing</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>6-Ball Matchups</td>
          <td>Low — exponential outcome combinations make accurate pricing extremely difficult for standard book models.</td>
          <td>Potentially highest profitability tier. Combinatorial mispricing at this scale may represent our largest exploitable edge.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:#FBF4E4;color:#A07828;">Under Investigation</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
